Nigerian singer, Temilade Openiyi, better known as Tems has been nominated for the 2021 BET Awards. The organizers took to their official Twitter account to announce nominations for the 2021 awards. The singer, together with other international artists got nominations for the Best New International Act award. BBNaija: Big Brother announces date for Season 6 audition, lists criteria “We are thrilled to announce this year’s Viewer’s Choice: Best New International Act Nominees; arloparks (UK),BramsitoB7 (France),breerunway (UK),Elaine (SA),mcdricka13 (Brazil),ronisia_mds (France) and temsbaby (Nigeria). “Go to @BET_INTL to cast your vote,” the tweet said. Popular Nigerian musicians, Wizkid and Burna Boy have also been nominated for the 2021 Bet Awards. Recall that Award-winning superstars, Ayodeji Ibrahim Balogun, popularly known as Wizkid, and Damini Ogulu, popularly known as Burna Boy, got a nomination each for the best “International Act” along with several other international artists.  